		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.scottsbasslessons.com/?p=11958#comment-16556</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[It&#039;s been a while since I&#039;ve auditioned, but a couple of lessons I learnt the hard way were &#039;If you&#039;re not given material to prepare with, keep it simple&#039; - too many notes lost me a tour with a great blues guitarist.   And if they ask for backing vocals, ask which harmonies - the high parts in Bee Gees disco were way beyond my range!


And, well you asked for stories :-) - A local club&#039;s resident band was auditioning bass players and drummers.  We were all shown into the waiting room to await our turns. One drummer brought his girlfriend with him.  He and I both scored the gig and having the same tastes, played together in many bands over the following years, but I never did tell him that his girlfriend and I had spent a night together the previous weekend!]]></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>It&#8217;s been a while since I&#8217;ve auditioned, but a couple of lessons I learnt the hard way were &#8216;If you&#8217;re not given material to prepare with, keep it simple&#8217; &#8211; too many notes lost me a tour with a great blues guitarist.   And if they ask for backing vocals, ask which harmonies &#8211; the high parts in Bee Gees disco were way beyond my range!</p>
<p>And, well you asked for stories :-) &#8211; A local club&#8217;s resident band was auditioning bass players and drummers.  We were all shown into the waiting room to await our turns. One drummer brought his girlfriend with him.  He and I both scored the gig and having the same tastes, played together in many bands over the following years, but I never did tell him that his girlfriend and I had spent a night together the previous weekend!</p>
]]></content:encoded>
