		<description><![CDATA[Great video and tips. What a pity that this didn&#039;t come few months earlier. Now I know what I did wrong on the last &quot;audition&quot; if you can call it this way ;) I had not to much auditions as I am not a professional musician, although I always wanted to be - but this is life and we cannot do to much about it? Wrong, yes we can, and I actually did something that seemed to be impossible and it was - at least for me at this stage. Ok it sounds like a mistery, but here it comes - this summer one of the most famous metal bands was searching for a touring bass player and it was quite urgent. They asked to record a video of playing one of their tunes (just the bass line without anything else). So I recorded it and sent it, but unfortunately I didn&#039;t get the job, and I know why. I was too much into it and it was so sudden so I thought that I couldn&#039;t miss the chance. And I blew it because of the rush. But I have learned something - you always should try and be proud of yourself that you did something. This led me also to review my skills and work on them stronger than ever, mainly thanks to the tips I got from SBL ;)]]></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Great video and tips. What a pity that this didn&#8217;t come few months earlier. Now I know what I did wrong on the last &#8220;audition&#8221; if you can call it this way ;) I had not to much auditions as I am not a professional musician, although I always wanted to be &#8211; but this is life and we cannot do to much about it? Wrong, yes we can, and I actually did something that seemed to be impossible and it was &#8211; at least for me at this stage. Ok it sounds like a mistery, but here it comes &#8211; this summer one of the most famous metal bands was searching for a touring bass player and it was quite urgent. They asked to record a video of playing one of their tunes (just the bass line without anything else). So I recorded it and sent it, but unfortunately I didn&#8217;t get the job, and I know why. I was too much into it and it was so sudden so I thought that I couldn&#8217;t miss the chance. And I blew it because of the rush. But I have learned something &#8211; you always should try and be proud of yourself that you did something. This led me also to review my skills and work on them stronger than ever, mainly thanks to the tips I got from SBL ;)</p>
