	<item>
		<title>By: Mark Hindman</title>
		<link>http://www.scottsbasslessons.com/bass-tips/13-essential-audition-tips-for-bass-players.html#comment-16545</link>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Mark Hindman]]></dc:creator>
		<pubDate>Thu, 08 Oct 2015 17:12:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.scottsbasslessons.com/?p=11958#comment-16545</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[The best prep for an audition is to play. Practice the song/s inside out. I&#039;ve found there is no substitute for that. Oh, and try to get some sleep. And one more thought, if you are going to an audition, the band is looking for someone like you, be that guy.  My biggest fear in going to my first audition was that I would screw up. Well, I did that, and in the end it didn&#039;t matter.  If you truly love what you do, it will show.]]></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>The best prep for an audition is to play. Practice the song/s inside out. I&#8217;ve found there is no substitute for that. Oh, and try to get some sleep. And one more thought, if you are going to an audition, the band is looking for someone like you, be that guy.  My biggest fear in going to my first audition was that I would screw up. Well, I did that, and in the end it didn&#8217;t matter.  If you truly love what you do, it will show.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
